Description Updated: I'm trying to get the AD user account for renewal of license.
NEA Published Reports - cannot access

1) To access and provide screenshots of the ".Active Directory Inventory" > "Active Directory Summary" Report, open NEA and navigate as follows:

 

Jobs > ".Active Directory Inventory" > "1-AD Scan" > "Results" > "Active Directory Summary".

a) Take a screenshot of the upper half of the report (pie charts)

b) Take a screenshot of the lower half of the report - it actaully should take about 3 screenshots.

 

2) To confirm users that should be able to access the NEA (or StealthAUDIT) Published Reports, open NEA (SA) and navigate to Settings > Access. Users must be configured at least with the role = "Report Viewer". Users configured with the Role = "Administrator" will be able to log into NEA Published Reports and view the reports.

What We've Learned Updated: +++++
NEA Published Reports
+++++
1) Reset the password for the user configured to run the "Netwrix Enterprise Auditor Web Server" service in "Services.msc".

2) In NEA > Settings > Access, end user must be granted at least "Report Viewer" Role.

3) In the NEA (StealthAUDIT) database, the end user must be a WINDOWS_USER for the SA/NEA database (and granted "db_datareader" and "db_datawriter" database role membership as that database user.
